Investor-User Connection Platform Documentation
Overview
The Investor-User Connection Platform is a web application designed to facilitate connections between investors and users seeking investment opportunities. The platform provides functionalities for user registration, login, profile management, and connection history tracking.

Features
User Registration and Login: Users can create accounts and log in to access their profiles.
Investor Registration and Login: Investors can register and manage their investment details.
Profile Management: Both users and investors can update their profiles.
Connection History: Users can view their past connections with investors.
Technologies Used
Java Servlet: For handling server-side logic.
JSP (JavaServer Pages): For rendering dynamic web content.
JDBC (Java Database Connectivity): For database interactions.
MySQL: As the database management system.
Maven: For project dependency management.
Getting Started
Prerequisites
Java Development Kit (JDK) 8 or above
Apache Tomcat or another servlet container
MySQL database
